# Fix Login and Signup Functionality Walkthrough

I have completed the tasks to fix the login and signup flow across the backend and the frontend.

## Changes Made
- **Backend response formatting:** Updated [authController.js](file:///D:/antigravity/server/controllers/authController.js) to return a flat `{ success: true, token, user }` object.
- **Frontend TS Types:** Updated the [AuthResponse](file:///D:/antigravity/client/src/types/index.ts#44-49) type in [types/index.ts](file:///D:/antigravity/client/src/types/index.ts) to expect the new flattened format.
- **Frontend Context:** Refactored [AuthContext.tsx](file:///D:/antigravity/client/src/context/AuthContext.tsx) to handle the new [AuthResponse](file:///D:/antigravity/client/src/types/index.ts#44-49) type and extract the fields correctly.
- **Frontend Auth Pages:** Rewrote the submit logic for both [LoginPage.tsx](file:///D:/antigravity/client/src/pages/auth/LoginPage.tsx) and [SignupPage.tsx](file:///D:/antigravity/client/src/pages/auth/SignupPage.tsx) using local state to capture values, utilize the central [fetchWithKind](file:///D:/antigravity/client/src/services/axiosWrapper.ts#26-58) Axios wrapper, set explicit global error messages upon failure, store the token/user upon success, and print explicit console logs as requested.

## Automated Verification Done
- Sent direct cURL requests to the API locally, verifying that both `/auth/login` and `/auth/signup` return the exact JSON structure we defined. 
- Sent direct cURL requests with incorrect credentials to verify the error response format.

## Manual Verification Required
Because the automated browser test isn't fully set up with the local frontend application, please perform the following manual test:

1. Open your browser and navigate to the frontend running at [http://localhost:5173/auth/signup](http://localhost:5173/auth/signup) or [http://localhost:5174/auth/signup](http://localhost:5174/auth/signup). (You may need to verify which port Vite spun up by checking the dev server terminal).
2. Open your browser Developer Tools (F12) and go to the **Console** tab to observe the debug logs.
3. Attempt to sign up with a test email and password.
4. Verify the console prints out:
   `[Auth] Signup Token received: true`
   `[Auth] Token stored in localStorage: true`
5. Verify you are automatically redirected to the home page or dashboard.
6. Verify your name/avatar is displayed in the UI, indicating global state caught the user.
7. Open the **Network** tab in dev tools. Make any API call (e.g. going to a protected page, fetching products). Look at the Request Headers and verify `Authorization: Bearer <your_token>` is present.
8. Log out.
9. Navigate to the login page. Attempt to login with an incorrect password and verify the red error banner appears.
10. Attempt to login with the correct password and verify similar success states (console prints, redirection, network headers).
